    <note type="biography">
        <p>Politician and journalist. MP for Aylesbury, 1757–63. Wrote <hi rend="italic">Essay on woman</hi> (1754), a parody of Alexander Pope’s <hi rend="italic">Essay on man</hi>. Convicted of libel for denouncing the prime minister and the king’s speech, 1763–4; in exile until 1768. Lord mayor of London, 1774–5. Returned to Parliament, 1774–90.</p></note>
